# Black · power · ambition

a colour of the pie of the MTG (MTG Arena) game-world — emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦Black:MTG:6b6c42⟧

**who —** Black, the colour of power, ambition, and death — the belief that the individual should get what they want, by any means.
**what —** One of the five colours: sacrifice, drain, reanimation, and ruthless tutoring, on the conviction that power is the only real currency.
**where —** On the black arc of the wheel, allied with blue and red, enemy of white and green.
**why —** Because Black is Magic's honest villain that isn't a villain — the colour brave enough to say it wants to win.
**how —** By paying any price (life, creatures, the future) to get the result, and refusing ever to be the victim.

**the seal —** Power is the only currency, and death is just a resource — I am not evil, only honest about what everyone wants.

